2081: ECC3         ;------------------------- Get File Size - 23 (35) -------------------------;
2082: ECC3         ;  This function returns the virtual size of the specified file. It does so ;
2083: ECC3         ; by setting the random record number (bytes 33-35) in the specified FCB to ;
2084: ECC3         ; the maximum 128-byte record number in the file. The virtual file size is  ;
2085: ECC3         ; calculated from the record address of the record following the end of the ;
2086: ECC3         ; file. Bytes 33 and 34 form a 16-bit value that contains the record number,;
2087: ECC3         ; with overflow indicated in byte 35. If byte 35 is 01, this means that the ;
2088: ECC3         ; file has the maximum record count of 65,536.                              ;
2089: ECC3         ;  If the function cannot find the file specified by the FCB, it returns    ;
2090: ECC3         ; with the random record field set to O.                                    ;
2091: ECC3         ;  You can use this function when you want to add data to the end of an     ;
2092: ECC3         ; existing file. By calling this function first, the random record bytes    ;
2093: ECC3         ; will be set to the end of file. Subsequent Write Random calls will write  ;
2094: ECC3         ; out records to this preset address.                                       ;
2095: ECC3         ;                                                                           ;
2096: ECC3         ;  Do not confuse the virtual file size with the actual file size. In a     ;
2097: ECC3         ; random file, if you write just a single CP/M record to record number      ;
2098: ECC3         ; 1000 and then call this function, it will return with the random record   ;
